# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Contact form — email delivery
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# This is the TEMPLATE (safe to commit — it has no password in it).
# Your real settings live in `.env` or `.env.local`, which git ignores.
#
# The form works in two modes:
#
#   1. SMTP_PASS empty -> messages are forwarded by FormSubmit.
#                         Needs no password, but requires a one-time
#                         "Activate Form" click, and mail usually lands
#                         in SPAM because it isn't sent from your Gmail.
#
#   2. SMTP_PASS set   -> sent straight from your own Gmail account.
#                         This is the one that lands in the INBOX.
#                         ** Recommended — fixes the spam problem. **
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
#
#  ⚠️  SMTP_PASS is NOT your normal Gmail password.
#      Google blocks those for apps. You need an "App Password".
#
# How to get it (about 2 minutes):
#   1. The Gmail account must have 2-Step Verification turned ON:
#      https://myaccount.google.com/signinoptions/two-step-verification
#   2. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#   3. Type any name (e.g. "Portfolio") and click Create
#   4. Google shows a 16-character code like: abcd efgh ijkl mnop
#   5. Paste it below WITHOUT the spaces -> abcdefghijklmnop
#   6. Restart the dev server:  npm run dev

SMTP_PASS=

# Optional — these defaults are already correct for Gmail.
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USER=awais.m4325@gmail.com
# CONTACT_TO_EMAIL=awais.m4325@gmail.com

# Your live site URL (only used by the FormSubmit fallback).
# SITE_ORIGIN=https://your-site.vercel.app
